1
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:16,267
I need to get something
in the quarters.

2
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,300
You're not allowed to come in.

3
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:19,000
I worked longer here than you.

4
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:20,133
Why did you take that?

5
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,100
Mom! Mom!

6
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,333
Raul! No!

7
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:26,667
You are Raul's accomplice!

8
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,500
You planned this together!

9
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:30,667
Bring that criminal
to the police station!

10
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:32,900
Whereof, the court
finds the accused,

11
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:35,333
Amanda Sta. Maria, guilty.

12
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:37,367
Why don't you listen to me?

13
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:40,033
Nothing will happen to you
if you stay near me!

14
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,567
Think about yourself!

15
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,133
About your future!

16
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,533
If you don't have a class,
you have work.

17
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:47,433
And if you're off work,
you have to do sports.

18
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,600
How can you get a boyfriend

19
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:50,200
if you don't have time
to mingle?

20
00:00:50,267 --> 00:00:51,500
Aren't you happy, Eden?

21
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:56,833
I only feel bad that my mom
didn't get to see me win.

22
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:59,233
- I'll just use the restroom.
- Okay.

23
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,833
We have an engine problem.

24
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,733
- Eden?
- Where's Yenyen?

25
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,033
Raichu, where's Yenyen?

26
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,133
I don't know, Coach!

27
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,400
- Yen!
- Eden!

28
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:13,500
Mayday! Mayday! Mayday!

29
00:01:13,567 --> 00:01:15,567
Preparing for
an emergency landing.

30
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:46,533
Help!

31
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:52,867
Help!

32
00:01:58,033 --> 00:01:59,100
That's mine!

33
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:00,033
It's mine!

34
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,267
Help!

35
00:03:57,033 --> 00:03:58,367
Amanda.

36
00:03:58,433 --> 00:03:59,967
Dindi?

37
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:01,667
Dindi.

38
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:03,700
They're about to release
the result of our appeal.

39
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:05,500
They're going to release me!

40
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,200
Is that true?

41
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:09,967
That's good news!

42
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,900
Eden will be happy.

43
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:15,100
- My God!
- Wait a minute.

44
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:19,000
Isn't she coming tonight
from Davao?

45
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:20,000
Yes. Let me call her.

46
00:04:20,067 --> 00:04:21,400
No, don't call her!

47
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,100
Why? I'm so excited.

48
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,567
Let's just wait for her.

49
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:31,233
I want to tell her the news
in person.

50
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:33,067
I want to surprise her.

51
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,067
Dindi!

52
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:40,533
If not for her,
I would have lost hope by now.

53
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:44,800
I owe her a lot.

54
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,500
Of course, Amanda.

55
00:04:46,567 --> 00:04:48,600
That's true.
That's why I'm so excited

56
00:04:48,667 --> 00:04:50,767
to see Eden's reaction.

57
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,667
Our Christmas came early
this year.

58
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:55,733
This is the best gift
for both of you.

59
00:04:56,933 --> 00:04:59,000
I'm so excited too.

60
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,333
I'm excited.

61
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,867
I can't wait to be with Eden.

62
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:06,233
We need to make plans.

63
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:08,300
I'm going to cook
something good.

64
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:09,867
My gosh, I need to make plans.

65
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,000
I need to plan a menu.

66
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:13,367
We'll never get separated
ever again.

67
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,733
Amanda...

68
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:20,333
Amanda...

69
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:34,533
Where am I?

70
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:43,867
Help!

71
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:51,800
Help!

72
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:24,333
Someone's here.

73
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:26,533
Someone's out here.

74
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:28,633
Miss Vinluan!

75
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:31,833
Raichu!

76
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,633
Miss Vinluan!

77
00:07:37,867 --> 00:07:38,833
Raichu!

78
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:43,800
Miss Vinluan!

79
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:30,400
How can you let this happen?

80
00:08:31,667 --> 00:08:35,100
How could the court favor
that criminal?

81
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:39,700
You have to do something!

82
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:43,100
The supreme court
has already decided.

83
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,300
We can't do anything about it.

84
00:08:44,367 --> 00:08:46,167
This can't happen, Attorney!

85
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:50,533
She killed our son!

86
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,500
She suffered 8 years in prison
already!

87
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:54,533
I don't care!

88
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:56,833
8 years is not enough!

89
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,567
And didn't she get
a 12-year sentence?

90
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:02,500
And even 12 years is not enough,
Attorney!

91
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:06,167
All the pain and suffering
she has caused us!

92
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,267
Rina, calm down!

93
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:09,667
You, too!

94
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:13,667
You didn't do anything to get
justice for our son's death!

95
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:15,533
What more do you want me to do?

96
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,800
I did everything you wanted.

97
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:18,400
I even bribed some people!

98
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,867
Nothing happened.

99
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:22,733
Amanda's free now.

100
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:23,800
What do you mean she's free?

101
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:25,433
She's only free from prison.

102
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:30,233
But she'll never get away
from my anger.

103
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:31,533
She will suffer!

104
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:35,367
She will suffer until death!

105
00:09:43,233 --> 00:09:44,700
Miss Vinluan!

106
00:09:46,433 --> 00:09:47,900
Raichu!

107
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:55,733
Is anyone out there?

108
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:58,333
Miss Vinluan!

109
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,133
Raichu!

110
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,633
Miss Vinluan!

111
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,567
Here, take your meds, Mom.

112
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:04,967
To heal your wounds.

113
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,100
Why did this happen to me?

114
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:22,467
Miss, it's not yet the end
of the world.

115
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:23,633
Just hang in there.

116
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,567
Mom, I will never give up.

117
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:35,100
We can have a moment
of weakness.

118
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:42,300
We can fall for a bit,
but we get up and fight.

119
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:45,467
Like people always say,
never give up.

120
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:48,300
Never give up.

121
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,667
No.

122
00:11:58,100 --> 00:12:01,700
You need to fight, Yenyen.

123
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,967
I still want to see my mom.

124
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,767
Is anyone else out there?

125
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:42,200
Rina, that's enough.

126
00:12:42,267 --> 00:12:43,300
You've had too much.

127
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,100
Leave me alone.

128
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,333
I'm so stressed out.

129
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:53,600
How can they let Amanda go?

130
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:54,767
Come on!

131
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:58,033
It's just not fair!

132
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,000
Your son is coming back
from Davao.

133
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:03,300
Do you want him
to see you drunk?

134
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:06,933
Wait a minute.

135
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:12,100
Isn't he supposed to be here
last night?

136
00:13:12,167 --> 00:13:14,900
Didn't he ask you for permission
before he left?

137
00:13:14,967 --> 00:13:16,700
He said he'd be staying
with Sab.

138
00:13:18,233 --> 00:13:19,767
He didn't give me a call.

139
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:26,033
Help!

140
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,333
Help!

141
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:29,767
Help!

142
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,667
Help!

143
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,133
Nila?

144
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:48,533
Nila, did Sab come home
last night with my son?

145
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,667
My daughter's also not home yet.

146
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,033
What?

147
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:55,833
Is their flight being delayed?

148
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,800
Didn't you hear the news?

149
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:00,700
What news?

150
00:14:00,767 --> 00:14:04,000
The plane never got
to the airport.

151
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,433
They say there's a chance
that the plane crashed.

152
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,167
No, no, no!

153
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:09,133
No!

154
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,267
Rina.

155
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:11,300
Rina, what's going on?

156
00:14:14,967 --> 00:14:18,233
Our son's plane didn't make it
to the airport.

157
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:22,800
There's a chance
that the plane crashed.

158
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:24,800
What?

159
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:27,900
Victor.

160
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:40,200
Help!

161
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:41,200
Help!

162
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,300
Help!

163
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:44,733
Miss!

164
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,333
Miss, hold on to me.

165
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,400
Hold on to me.

166
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,133
Come on, Miss.

167
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:09,900
Everyone's already on the move,
Sir.

168
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:12,133
It's just hard
because they can't pinpoint

169
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:14,333
the exact location of the crash.

170
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,800
What are the chances
that my son is still alive?

171
00:15:16,867 --> 00:15:18,933
I can't give you an answer
right now, Sir.

172
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,233
Please...

173
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,533
do everything you can.

174
00:15:22,567 --> 00:15:24,167
Save my son.

175
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:28,400
I don't care how much
it will cost us.

176
00:15:28,467 --> 00:15:29,433
Rina.

177
00:15:30,767 --> 00:15:31,733
Victor...

178
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:35,000
we already lost a son.

179
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:39,800
I don't want to lose
another one.

180
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:42,633
Please, Victor.

181
00:15:44,467 --> 00:15:46,867
I want my son home...

182
00:15:46,933 --> 00:15:48,000
alive.

183
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:50,433
I want him home alive, please.

184
00:15:55,233 --> 00:15:56,533
Thank you. Thank you.

185
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,533
I thought
I was the only survivor.

186
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:00,967
Are you okay?

187
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:02,067
Yeah, I'm good.

188
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,567
It's you.

189
00:16:20,167 --> 00:16:21,533
You look familiar.

190
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,967
You're the guy at the campus.

191
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,133
Yeah, dude. We'll chill.

192
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,233
Yeah, I just need
to run an errand.

193
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,400
I'll see you later.

194
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:38,533
Yes, see you.

195
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:29,767
Miss, it's not yet the end
of the world.

196
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:30,967
Just hang in there.

197
00:17:52,633 --> 00:17:54,867
You look so tired that day.

198
00:17:54,933 --> 00:17:57,400
I felt your frustration.

199
00:17:57,467 --> 00:17:58,800
I can actually relate.

200
00:18:00,733 --> 00:18:02,100
That's true.

201
00:18:02,167 --> 00:18:04,167
Your message helped me.

202
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:08,733
As athletes, we have to be ready
at all times.

203
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:11,467
We may fall sometimes,

204
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:13,533
but what matters
is we get back on our feet.

205
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,867
By the way, I'm Red.

206
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,500
Just call me Yenyen.

207
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,167
That's what my friends call me.

208
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:25,967
And my mom too.

209
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:31,800
I know.

210
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,767
I know, I miss my parents too.

211
00:18:36,567 --> 00:18:39,933
I hope there are
other survivors.

212
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:48,400
Never give up.

213
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,200
That's what you said, right?

214
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:55,200
Yes, never give up.

215
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,567
Let's go.

216
00:18:58,633 --> 00:19:00,000
Let's go look
for other survivors.

217
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:19,567
God, thank you so much.

218
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:24,467
I nearly lost hope
for being here for so long.

219
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:31,133
But I will be free now.

220
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:35,533
Lord, thank you so much.

221
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:37,967
It took a while,

222
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:43,067
but I won't dwell
on the lost time anymore.

223
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:47,033
I will be with my daughter now,
and that's all that matters.

224
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:50,867
We will never be apart anymore.

225
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,467
Miss Vinluan!

226
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:01,367
Raichu!

227
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:03,533
Are they with you on the plane?

228
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:05,833
Yes. Raichu's my best friend.

229
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,767
And Miss Vinluan
is my coach and mentor.

230
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,600
I hope they survived.

231
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,567
I'm with a friend too.

232
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:13,600
I hope she survived too.

233
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:15,567
Let's keep looking.

234
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,333
They might need our help.

235
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,300
Let's go!

236
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:20,300
Yenyen!

237
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:45,100
Cell phone!

238
00:20:45,167 --> 00:20:46,333
Cell phone!

239
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,367
Let me see.

240
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:52,200
There's a signal and battery!

241
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,267
It's working!

242
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,700
Red, let me have it, please.

243
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:55,833
I need to call my aunt.

244
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,900
My mom needs to know
that I'm alive.

245
00:20:57,967 --> 00:20:59,100
Wait.

246
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:01,900
Okay. I understand that you want
to talk to your family.

247
00:21:01,967 --> 00:21:04,400
But let's be practical
right now, okay?

248
00:21:04,467 --> 00:21:05,933
I'll call my dad.

249
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,233
Red, I can ask my aunt for help.

250
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,900
- Let me have it.
- No, my dad has resources.

251
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,267
He has connections. In no time,

252
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,533
the rescuers will be here
to help us.

253
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,933
You will go home, promise.

254
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:15,967
Okay?

255
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:27,233
I'll try again.

256
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,400
- Give it to me.
- I'll try again.

257
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:29,433
Wait.

258
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,400
- Come on.
- Red, let me make a call.

259
00:21:34,467 --> 00:21:35,533
- The battery might die. Please.
- Wait.

260
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,700
I want to call my mom.

261
00:21:36,767 --> 00:21:38,267
Okay, let me call my mom
instead, okay?

262
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:40,200
Your mom might not take
your call either.

263
00:21:40,267 --> 00:21:42,100
My mom will answer the phone.

264
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,800
Trust me. She'll answer
the phone.

265
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:50,933
Red, let me make a call.

266
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,833
Wait, please,
let me make this call, okay?

267
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:55,633
Mom, please!

268
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,867
She's not answering her phone.
Give it to me.

269
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:02,967
- Let me make a call!
- I'll do it.

270
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:04,000
- Give it to me.
- Let me do it.

271
00:22:04,067 --> 00:22:05,033
- Don't be stubborn.
- Let me make a call.

272
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,267
- Give it to me!
- Let me have it!

273
00:22:06,333 --> 00:22:07,533
- I'll make the call!
- Let me have it!

274
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:23,500
Look at what happened!

275
00:22:23,567 --> 00:22:25,000
It's not working anymore!

276
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:27,733
It's all your fault!

277
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,300
- Why are you blaming me?
- You wasted our chance!

278
00:22:35,567 --> 00:22:38,000
If only you let me call my aunt.

279
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:39,767
We could at least ask for help.

280
00:22:41,367 --> 00:22:42,700
Where are your resources now?

281
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:44,200
Where's your dad?

282
00:22:44,267 --> 00:22:45,500
Where are they?

283
00:22:45,567 --> 00:22:46,767
Don't blame me, okay?

284
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:48,000
You wasted our chance!

285
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,867
Stop blaming me!

286
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:52,067
We both want to go home!

287
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:54,800
We both have a family
waiting for us!

288
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,900
Yes, we're in the same boat.

289
00:22:56,967 --> 00:22:59,367
So why are you calling
all the shots?

290
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:00,933
Because you're rich?

291
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,067
Because you're wealthy?

292
00:23:02,133 --> 00:23:04,567
I did what's practical, okay?

293
00:23:06,067 --> 00:23:07,933
I didn't know it would end up
like this!

294
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:13,300
You don't know what my mom and I
went through.

295
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:17,433
We need to be together!

296
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,233
Don't lose hope, okay?

297
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:44,033
The mere fact that we're alive
and safe...

298
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:47,033
that we didn't die...

299
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:48,767
we will survive, okay?

300
00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:51,433
We never know. There might be
rescuers coming our way.

301
00:23:52,467 --> 00:23:54,667
You will go home.
You will see your mom.

302
00:23:57,300 --> 00:24:00,000
How will the rescuers find us?

303
00:25:03,867 --> 00:25:06,800
I'm confident that rescuers
will be here anytime soon.

304
00:25:06,867 --> 00:25:10,967
We need to find food,
water, and shelter.

305
00:25:11,033 --> 00:25:13,633
We can only get that done
if we help each other out.

306
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,467
We'll help each other out
from now on.

307
00:25:15,533 --> 00:25:16,500
Deal.

308
00:25:16,567 --> 00:25:19,767
The plane that Yenyen
boarded back to Manila

309
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,000
is nowhere to be found.

310
00:25:21,067 --> 00:25:22,900
It might have crashed, Amanda.

311
00:25:22,967 --> 00:25:24,733
Do the rescuers have a lead yet?

312
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,733
Where is our son?

313
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,233
They can't give us
any information for now.

314
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:30,433
Of course,
they're searching the area

315
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:32,267
where the plane
could have crashed.

316
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:34,567
But there's a lot of area
and island to look into.

317
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:36,000
It will take some time.

318
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:37,967
It's all Ramoses' fault.

319
00:25:38,033 --> 00:25:41,500
If only they hadn't accused me,
I wouldn't be in this prison.

320
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:43,800
My daughter and I
wouldn't be separated.

321
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:45,367
Why?

322
00:25:45,433 --> 00:25:47,267
What happened to you
and your mother?

323
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:48,900
We got separated.

324
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:53,000
My mom went to jail.

325
00:25:53,067 --> 00:25:54,133
What?

326
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:56,267
Someone cruel person
put her in prison.
